It seems Netflix has found a market for African content. The US-based streaming service provider recently announced it has added Gangster's Paradise: Jerusalema to its platform, starting from Friday, 1 May. ALSO READ:6 HAIR REMOVAL TIPS FOR SMOOTH SKIN! The popular movie starring talented actor Rapulana Seiphemo follows the life of a small-time thug who builds a criminal empire in Joburg, but a growing war with a druglord and police pressure threaten to shut him down. The local movie is one of many with Mzansi content being added to the streaming service. It recently added Four Corners, How To Steal 2 Million, Baby Mamas, Tsotsi and White Wedding. SEE POST BELOW:   